, '2014-07-30 14:53:06', '2014-07-30 14:53:06', '<h4>Hi. I’m Harry.</h4>
<p class="p2">With this first ever blog post I wish to introduce myself and tell you about the trials I go through striving for self-employment. Disillusioned with corporate faux-familiarity, ethos, culture (sorry to all those exceptions), I’ve turned to code. Legit. I did a degree in law and now, with no prior experience, I’m going to totally change direction and turn to web-development. My last job with <a title="Free:Formers Home" href="http://freeformers.com/" target="_blank">Free:Formers</a> introduced me to a potential to which I am devoting my hopes and expectations for the future. Along the way to reaching freelance status, the name for which I am still yet to decide (front-runners are, so far, race to freelance or super portfolio developer 2000), I’ll be building working websites and I’ll be working to support my study and practice. This means stop-gap job(s) which might herald some good readin\' for you too!</p>
<p class="p2">Anyway, the reason I want you to watch this space is because I want your feedback on what I’ve got, what I could do better, what you want to see made etc and I want you to tell other people I’m doing it. The reason you should watch this space is because it’ll be cool, you know, seeing things get better and better each time. It’ll be like watching one of those time-lapses of fruit going rotten but <a title="Reversed rotting fruit" href="http://a.gifb.in/012011/reverse-1296151218_fruit-and-vegetable-decomposing-74-days.gif" target="_blank">in reverse</a>. And I want it to be an entertaining read. And you get the power of legitimately ripping someone’s hard work to pieces with no hard feelings. Who doesn’t like to indulge that urge? C’mon. Yeah, I know I’m late to the code party, but at least I’m not the last! Who can fault a guy for trying? Or coming in fancy dress.</p>
<p class="p2">So, here’s the big idea: I’ll build 50 websites by New Year’s Eve. Maybe it doesn’t sound like much, maybe it does. It gives me roughly 30 weeks or 7 months. Maybe it’ll be more than 50! There will be a lot of variation though, some of them will be simple static pages, others not so static, others full-fledged sites! The campaign is either going to be #digitalhustlehalfcentury or “Don’t just surf, #makewaves”. Pretty catchy right? Something less pretentious? Gotcha.</p>


<hr />
<p class="p2"><strong>How’s this going to work, mate?</strong></p>
<p class="p2">Firstly, I’ll be building websites with <a title="Sublime Text Editor" href="http://www.sublimetext.com/" target="_blank">Sublime Text Editor</a>; learning from <a title="Harry Fox on Treehouse" href="http://teamtreehouse.com/harryfox" target="_blank">Team Treehouse</a>, Google, and cleverer people than I; and posting pages either with external jsbin links or something else for your inspection. There should be at least 1 of these a week.</p>
<p class="p2">Secondly, I’m going to post a blog (less enthusiastically than websites because they’re a narcissistic indulgence on my part and I can only feel embarrassed so many days of the week). That’ll be to tell stories, give some proper context to the websites, and to divulge the inspiration and issues associated with it. There’ll probably be 1 of these a week too. <a title="Harry Fox Twitter" href="https://twitter.com/harrygfox" target="_blank">@harrygfox</a></p>


<hr />
<p class="p1"><strong><span class="s1">Now what?</span></strong></p>
<p class="p2">Now I’ll be trying everything, experimenting, making mistakes and showing you the products. I\'ll blog again soon, but in the mean time <a title="5 Bad Habits" href="http://www.harryfox.me/portfolio/5badhabits.html" target="_blank">here is my first page.</a></p>
<p class="p1"><span class="s1">With gratitude,</span></p>
<p class="p1"><span class="s1">Harry Fox</span></p>', 'Young person wanting to make it in code. No Experience experienced. £0pw.', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'young-person-wanting-to-make-it-in-code-no-experience-experienced-0pw-2', '', '', '2014-07-30 14:54:08', '2014-07-30 14:54:08', '', 0, 'http://localhost/harryfox.me/?p=31', 0, 'post', '', 0) ; 
