So, I wrote myself a brief and here it is):
<p style="text-align: right;"><strong>Brief for webpage</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: right;">"After some reflective thought in the shower the other day I felt the need to confess to some of the terrible things I have done to the people I have lived with in the last few years.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;">I\'d like a website that will tastefully reveal 5 bad habits of mine that my conscience compels me to reveal to my flatmates old and new."</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Pre-build design</strong></p>
<a href="http://harryfox.me/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/IMG_6688.jpg"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-28" src="http://harryfox.me/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/IMG_6688-1024x768.jpg" alt="IMG_6688" width="307" height="230" /></a> <a href="http://harryfox.me/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/ideamap.jpg"><img class="wp-image-27 aligncenter" src="http://harryfox.me/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/ideamap-1024x768.jpg" alt="ideamap" width="363" height="272" /></a><a href="http://harryfox.me/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/mobilemockup.jpg"><img class="wp-image-29 alignleft" src="http://harryfox.me/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/mobilemockup-768x1024.jpg" alt="mobilemockup" width="179" height="239" /><img class="wp-image-31 alignright" src="http://harryfox.me/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/webmockup-1024x768.jpg" alt="webmockup" width="210" height="157" /></a><a href="http://harryfox.me/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Mockup.png"> <img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-30" src="http://harryfox.me/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Mockup-1024x426.png" alt="Mockup" width="474" height="197" /></a> <a href="http://harryfox.me/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/webmockup.jpg">
</a> <a href="http://harryfox.me/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/bugok.jpg"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-32" src="http://harryfox.me/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/bugok.jpg" alt="bugok" width="318" height="238" /></a>

<strong>Post-build de-brief</strong>

<!--more-->

I\'m pretty happy with the final look and feel of the site. I spent far too long messing about with colours and positioning, but I couldn\'t control myself. The total build time was about two full days. Certainly, this could be drastically cut down in future projects as I get more savvy with using bootstrap. Having a cross-platform design in mind ahead of time would probably be a very good idea for next time.

For bigger projects, it might also be a good idea to, at some stage, label colours and more specifics in the mockup so that I need not spend as much time messing around with borders and finding that perfect shade of off-white for the cards.

I came up with the idea for a card-flip as a nice way to reveal, without too much tension, the confession hidden on the reverse of the card. I toyed with the idea of making the cards into top-trump cards or Pokémon cards but eventually settled on playing cards. The background was always going to look like a table surface, but I ditched the green felt look of a real card-table for the mahogany wood which felt prettier and more suited to the "tasteful" theme I specified in the original brief.

